[08:50.35]	It irks his heart he cannot be revenged.
[08:55.22]	Frenchmen, I'll be a Salisbury to you:
[08:59.77]	Pucelle or puzzel, dolphin or dogfish,
[09:04.33]	Your hearts I'll stamp out with my horse's heels,
[09:10.15]	And make a quagmire of your mingled brains.
[09:15.34]	Convey me Salisbury into his tent,
[09:19.58]	And then we'll try what these dastard Frenchmen dare.
